<http://dx.doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.3629.1.1>
    bibo:endPage "106" ;
    bibo:issue "1" ;
    bibo:journal "Zootaxa" ;
    bibo:pubDate "2013-03-18" ;
    bibo:startPage "1" ;
    bibo:volume "3629" ;
    dc:creator "Blank, Stephan M.; Shinohara, Akihiko; Altenhofer, Ewald" ;
    dc:date "2013" ;
    dc:title "<strong> The Eurasian species of <em> Xyela </ em> (Hymenoptera, Xyelidae): taxonomy, host plants and distribution </ strong>" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5261370>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5261378>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5261376>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5261384>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5261386>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5261362>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5261368> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5261370>
    dc:description "FIGURES 24–41. Color pattern of head of Xyela species: X. longula group, X. lugdunensis group, X. alpigena group, X. meridionalis group. Legend: HT—holotype; LT—lectotype; PT—paratype. Legend for Fig. 25: kss—kidney-shaped spot; mfs—medial frontal spot; sff—stripe along frontal furrow." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5261370/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5261378>
    dc:description "FIGURES 95–104. Ovipositor sheaths of Xyela species. All figures at same scale. Legend: HT—holotype; PT—paratype." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5261378/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5261376>
    dc:description "FIGURES 86–94. Ovipositor sheath, sensilla pattern and sensilla plate (spl) at the apex of the ovipositor sheath. 86, Xyela helvetica. 87, X. longula, arrows indicate the modified hairs at apex of valvula 1. 88, X. lugdunensis. 89, X. meridionalis. 90–91, X. alpigena. 92–93, X. curva. 94, X. densiflorae." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5261376/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5261384>
    dc:description "FIGURES 121–125. Distal section of ovipositors. 121, Xyela longula. 122, X. alpigena. 123, X. occidentalis (paratype). 124, X. curva. 125, X. rasnitsyni (paratype). Arrowheads in Figs 123–124 indicate preapical small tooth on dorsal edge of valvula 1." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5261384/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5261386>
    dc:description "FIGURES 126–135. Penis valves of Xyela species: X. longula groups, X. lugdunensis group, X. alpigena group, X. meridionalis group. 127, tentatively identified male of from Tence (France: Auvergne, MNHN), see text. 128, paratype of X. nigroabscondita." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5261386/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5261362>
    dc:description "FIGURE 20. Records of Xyela longula (49 specimens from 32 collection sites) and natural distribution of the host plant, Pinus sylvestris (solid line, combined from Mirov 1967, Sokolov et al. 1977 and Willis et al. 1998). Two additional records included from Scotland (Harwood 1950, Entwistle 1996). The question mark refers to a tentatively identified male from Tence (France: Auvergne; see text)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5261362/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5261368>
    dc:description "FIGURE 23. Barcoding analysis of Xyela species. The tree is primarily based on specimens for which COI sequences longer than 600 bp and including less than three ambigous nucleotides could be obtained. Some shorter sequences have been added to associate sexes or larvae with imagines. Each specimen is labelled as follows: “Xyela ...”—species name; “DEIGISHym ...”—unique identification number of specimen in DEI collection; “Male / Female”—sex, larva if no sex is indicated; e.g., “661” / “603” / “658” ...—base pairs [bp] sequence length; “[0n] / [1n] / [2n]”—0–2 ambiguous nucleotides included in sequence; e.g., “Austria, Karnten [= Kärnten, Carinthia]”—country and province of origin of specimen; “BOLD: ...”—globally unique identifier (GUID). The label “Xyela 005 P. sabiniana sp.” refers to larvae obtained from Pinus sabiniana which here are identified as X. bakeri." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5261368/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

